2019-12-19 12:32:02	FromGitter	<randiaz95> Guys, is there normally a rule of thumb when it comes to IO over 2 programming languages? ⏎  ⏎ For example: Should I run an executable from my api gateway with some sort of child process crystal executable or should I send a post request over localhost on a server that is listening in crystal?
2019-12-19 12:33:41	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> probably the former is better for small projects and the latter for large ones
2019-12-19 12:34:15	FromGitter	<randiaz95> Is it because the benefits of large programs are that it can be run over 2 different computers or servers?
2019-12-19 12:34:40	FromGitter	<randiaz95> I was thinking performance could be faster for http server because the overhead of booting up a language is still a little there in terms of an executable.
2019-12-19 12:34:53	FromGitter	<randiaz95> also, I can keep long term variables and datastructs
2019-12-19 12:35:53	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> as a compiled language Crystal has minimal run-time initialization
2019-12-19 12:36:27	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> it's not Ruby :)
2019-12-19 12:36:53	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> even PHP boots in a few dozen milliseconds or so
2019-12-19 12:38:00	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> but yes, on the large scale, you may end up with different machines for the different processes, and for that you'd want an API
2019-12-19 12:38:26	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> you could split the difference and use some sort of job queue that would invoke a Crystal binary
2019-12-19 12:39:02	FromGitter	<tenebrousedge> something like beanstalkd
